LAGOS – The Lagos State chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has condoled with the families of victims of Friday’s petrol tanker explosion in Lagos State. In a press statement, released by the state Publicity Secretary, Hakeem Amode, the party sent its condolence message to the families of the victims of the fire incident which was reported to have occurred in the early hours of Friday, where a petrol tanker crashed and exploded at Ajegunle bus stop, Alagbado, on the Lagos-Abeokuta expressway. The incident which happened around 3:am did not only burn down houses and shops but trapped and killed some yet to be confirmed number of people. The PDP also requested that the  All Progressives Congress  (APC) government should investigate the cause of the accident, take immediate action and to endure the prosecution of the owners of the tanker if negligence is detected. “We urge that the ruling party should put necessary measures in place to endure that our tis are road users and also make necessary laws that must put an end to recklessness on our roads. “The Lagos State PDP can not overemphasise the safety of our roads snd the need to have in place policies, endure proper implementation that will guarantee the safety of lives and properties of Lagosians,” the statement read.